#### 3. Technological Innovations

**3.1 Cellular Compartmentalization:** Modular design with interconnected cells (~50 mÂ³ each) for failure isolation. 3D-printed regolith bulkheads via microwave sintering (>10 MPa strength).

Conceptual Mars habitats featuring cellular designs, regolith 3D printing, and inflatable/ice structures for compartmentalized resilience.

**3.2 Nitrogen/Argon Extraction:** Enhanced closed-loop via PSA/TSA (~1â€“2 kWh/kg). Maintains partial pressures per Dalton's Law:

\[ P_{\text{total}} = P_{\text{O}_2} + P_{\text{N}_2} + P_{\text{Ar}} + P_{\text{CO}_2} + P_{\text{H}_2\text{O}} \]

Reduces fire risk and leakage losses.

Pressure Swing Adsorption (PSA) process diagrams, showing cycles for selective gas separation from COâ‚‚-dominant atmospheres.

**3.3 Regolith 3D Printing:** Robotic extrusion/sintering for on-site construction.

