#### 8. Implementation Roadmap (2026â€“2030)

To move from white paper to off-world deployment, the following milestones are required. This roadmap focuses on validating the System Governor AI and Nitrogen/Argon Scrubber prototype.

Phase 1: Terrestrial Prototype & Analog Integration (2026)
 * Q1-Q2: Prototype a modular PSA (Pressure Swing Adsorption) unit using JSC Mars-1A simulants for dust filtration testing.
 * Q3: Conduct a "Shadow Simulation" during the final months of CHAPEA Mission 2 (ending Oct 2026). Use Mission 2â€™s published telemetry to feed your AI System Governor, comparing the AIâ€™s theoretical tactical decisions against the human crew's actual responses.
 * Q4: Deploy a "Level 2 Tactical AI" unit to MDRS (Utah) for a 2-week field rotation to manage GreenHab humidity and power distribution.

Phase 2: Closed-Loop Stress Testing (2027â€“2028)
 * Isolation Trials: Execute a 180-day "Digital Twin" simulation. Use Blender/Unity to simulate the habitat with a 0.5% daily air leak and a 4-month global dust storm.
 * Verification: Apply Formal Methods to the AI Strategic Layer to ensure it cannot "hallucinate" or override critical life-support safety protocols.

Phase 3: Uncrewed Mars Demonstration (2029)
 * Mission Concept: A "Pre-Positioned ISRU Lander."
 * Goal: Successfully harvest 10 kg of Oâ‚‚ and 50 kg of Nâ‚‚/Ar from the Martian atmosphere using the protocols outlined in Section 3.2.

